18/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania's Supreme Defence Council decided at its latest session held Thursday (15 April) that the country would not withdraw its troops from Iraq. Romanian President Ion Iliescu said there was no other alternative to the international coalition's presence in Iraq and that a withdrawal would not be a solution.
In other news, Romania's first wind power plant was inaugurated near the southern town of Ploiesti Saturday. Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and Minister of Economy Dan Ioan Popescu attended the formal ceremony for the launch of the 700 kw power generation facility. (Novinite.com, Rompres - 17/04/04; Rompres - 16/04/04)
